~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
This is INSTALL file for Configurator (C++ library for configuration file parsing).

Last update: November 30, 2010
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

CONFIGURATOR
version 0.9.2

Building doues not required. Just copy 'configurator' folder in some place where 
your compiler is looking for header files and add:
 
#include <configurator/configurator.hpp> 

in your program.


IMPORTANT!

If you want use Singleton-variant of cf::configurator class, compile program with flag WITH_SINGLETON.
If you want use semantics check, compile program with flag WITH_SEMANTIC_CHECK.

Example:

# g++ -DWITH_SINGLETON -DWITH_SEMANTIC_CHECK -o test main.cpp -lboost_system -lboost_filesystem -lboost_regex -lboost_thread
